Signatures:

(C::CrvHyp, kernel::RngUPolElt[RngUPolRes]) -> .
(J::JacHyp, kernel::RngUPolElt[RngUPolRes]) -> .

Given a Jacobian of a genus 2 curve together with a description of a maximal isotropic exponent 2 kernel, return a description of the codomain. This can be again a Jacobian of a genus 2 curve, a product of elliptic curves or an elliptic curve over quadratic extension, representing its weil restriction to the ground field. See documentation for a description of how to describe a kernel.


